========= 	Samaritans 		=========
Samaritans or 'Cutheans' are were a very early ethnic group, widely extended from Assyria to India, China, Arabia Petraea and Abyssinia, and rich and powerful. They were impoted by the Assyrian Empire also to Samaria, in a politic of mass-deportations. They had their Samaritan Temple on Mt. Gerizim, opposed to the Temple in Jerusalem, and they worshiped the mesopotamian deity Nergal, his emblem was a cock.


